======================================================================
DEEP DIVE 1: H AS EIGENFUNCTION OF HYPERCUBE ADJACENCY
======================================================================

  n=3 (m=3):
    Z = sum of H(neighbors)
    Best fit: Z = -1.000000 * H + 6.000000
    Max residual: 0.0000000000
    *** EXACT: Z = -1.0 * H + 6.0 ***
    Eigenvalue interpretation: lambda = -1.0
    m = 3, so m - lambda = 4.0, (m-lambda)/2 = 2.0
    H - 1.500000*1 is eigenvector of Q_3 adjacency with eigenvalue -1.0

  n=4 (m=6):
    Z = sum of H(neighbors)
    Best fit: Z = 2.000000 * H + 12.000000
    Max residual: 0.0000000000
    *** EXACT: Z = 2.0 * H + 12.0 ***
    Eigenvalue interpretation: lambda = 2.0
    m = 6, so m - lambda = 4.0, (m-lambda)/2 = 2.0
    H - 3.000000*1 is eigenvector of Q_6 adjacency with eigenvalue 2.0

  n=5 (m=10):
    Z = sum of H(neighbors)
    Best fit: Z = 5.789474 * H + 31.578947
    Max residual: 10.4210526316
    NOT exactly affine. Checking quadratic...
    Z values by H class:
      H=   1: Z in [32]
      H=   3: Z in [48]
      H=   5: Z in [64]
      H=   9: Z in [84]
      H=  11: Z in [100]
      H=  13: Z in [104]
      H=  15: Z in [108, 120]

