======================================================================
DEEP DIVE 12: MÖBIUS FUNCTION ON H-SPECTRUM ORDER
======================================================================

  Define a PARTIAL ORDER on the H-spectrum:
  h1 <= h2 if there exists a sequence of arc flips
  T_1 -> T_2 -> ... -> T_k where H(T_1) = h1, H(T_k) = h2,
  and H is non-decreasing along the path.

  This defines the "H-reachability order."

  For n=4: Can we reach H=5 from H=1 via non-decreasing H path?
  For n=5: What's the Hasse diagram of this order?


  n=4: H-reachability:
    From H=1: can reach [1, 3, 5]
    From H=3: can reach [3, 5]
    From H=5: can reach [5]

  n=5: H-reachability:
    From H=1: can reach [1, 3, 5, 9, 11, 13, 15]
    From H=3: can reach [3, 5, 9, 11, 13, 15]
    From H=5: can reach [5, 9, 11, 13, 15]
    From H=9: can reach [9, 11, 13, 15]
    From H=11: can reach [11, 13, 15]
    From H=13: can reach [13, 15]
    From H=15: can reach [15]
    Reachability order is TOTAL

